Description: Tangible Instruments is the producer of Arpeggio, a mobile device for musical artists to create melodies.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Tangible creates instruments that follow a consistent, clean design aesthetic and user experience, each focused on a fundamental musical element like harmony, melody, and rhythm. We understand that having a feature that someone can intuitively use is more important than having two they can’t. Instruments with inspired design inspire better music. Competitors are designing electronic instruments for electronic musicians, their thought process is not concerned with people who aren’t. At our earliest design stages we ask how do we design tools not only for professionals but also for drawing future musicians in? How do we make something that feels inviting and inclusive? No one else seems to be asking. Electronic instruments today create barriers to creativity. Hardware is complex and unmusical, software instruments aren't inspiring, products generally lack focus. Humans crave self expression and we need the right tools to do so. After hundreds of years, instruments like guitars, violins and pianos have been perfected. Electronic instruments haven't yet. We want to expand the market of electronic musicians by removing technical barriers and designing focused and simple ways to create music.
Industry Groups: Consumer Electronics, Education, Hardware, Media and Entertainment, Music and Audio, Other
Founders: Charlie Lesoine, Maxfield Rosenzweig, Nicholas Morrow, Viktor Metelev

OUR VISION We think everybody should have the opportunity to travel the world. We imagine a planet where our differences don't divide us, where our dissimilarities are a source of inspiration and development, not xenophobia and prejudice. We hope to achieve our dream of a diversified world by making travel cheaper and encouraging each of us to stay curious and be progressive.   OUR MISSION Our mission at Airporia is to empower you to make confident decisions when purchasing flights, hotels, and car rentals. We see our site as more than just an excellent search tool; it takes you one step closer to where you need to be. ABOUT THE FOUNDER  Nasib Gul founded Airporia in 2021. His business is based in Michigan, where he resides with his family. Nasib enjoys traveling and staying active, and this website is his way to share that joy with everyone on earth. At Airporia, we’re excited to connect you with the best travel deals, and we take great pride in fueling your mission to see the world for less. TRAVEL BLOG Our travel blog is a fascinating section curated by Nasib! It features luxury hotels, things to do, destinations, tips, and news. Description: This Food Blog is based in Minneapolis, Minnesota. Thank you for reading our recipe food blog.
Headquarters Regions: Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: This amazing Food Blog is based in Minneapolis, Minnesota. Thank you for reading our recipe food blog. We are an online based food blogging website with a special interest in creating unique recipes for our readers. The onlinefoodblog.com stated about ten years ago - with me reading vast quantities of food recipes online and purchasing cookbooks every time I visited a bookstore. I only started my own food blog 2 years ago as I was working full time at that stage. As you probably gathered I am bit obsessed with creating amazing recipes for my readers that is tasty and easy to make. I began loving food at the age of 16 while working at various food chains for extra spending money. At some stage I got a history lesson from some of the world class chefs about how different food groups combine to create a new taste. I also start to realise the difference between developing your own recipes from an existing recipe to just following the recipe that you read online or in a cookbook.  Food blogging is easy but only if you enjoy making food. Sitting hours behind a computer writing out various recipe ideas and then testing them can become choir if you don’t enjoy making food.   I do not consider myself a professional cook but rather a professional food recipe tester. I say this because I like to test different food options using an existing recipe. I would for instance not use salt in recipe but rather substitute it with seasoning that would give the recipe a different taste that may sometimes improve the recipe or totally ruin the whole thing. My food obsession includes dark chocolate and cookies. You will notice my preference when you read my food blog.

Description: DEO helps consumers to track price of things they want to buy and auto-purchase when the price is right.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: What is DEO? No, it’s not a new sci-fi character, and it’s not an acronym. DEO is your personal shopper online. A plug-in for your browser that works with an app to make sure you never miss a deal.  Think of it this way. How many times have you been online and found the perfect pair of jeans? I mean, the look, the fit, the color—everything was perfect.  Yet, you didn’t know if the price was what you were willing to pay. So instead of pulling the trigger, you went back to that same site every day for a week. Checking the price each time, only to see it never moved. So you passed on the jeans.  Only to hear from your friendly, yet boastful neighbor, he got the jeans on a one-day sale. The one day, you didn’t look.  Well, DEO can help with that. You see DEO tracks your wish list items, constantly checking the price of not only the original site, but other sites that might have the same item.  Then it notifies you when the price drops. So you’ll never miss a deal again.  DEO also simplifies the buying procedure. A few simple clicks from your DEO app purchases the item you want, without having to return back to the website. So you can get those perfect jeans, right from the palm of your hand.  So how does DEO work? Well, it’s rather simple really. When you’re online shopping, simply right-click the item you want DEO to track. Scroll down to TRACK ITEM WITH DEO.  Then, all you have to do is answer a few questions.  Then you can sit back, while DEO does all the work for you.  When the price drops, DEO will notify you right on your phone. Simply open the app, click “Buy Now”--and boom--those jeans are yours.  But DEO doesn’t just track prices; it also gives you a price forecast. Based on a lot of mathematical stuff that we won’t bore you with, we’ll tell you the probability that the price of your item might drop.  And DEO doesn’t stop there, because we want to be more than an app, we want to be your friend. So like any good friend, we’ll suggest things we think you might like in our Recommendations section.  So you can stay on top of the trends in fashion, home décor, electronics. Just about anything by seeing other items that people bought on DEO in our Trending section. So next time you see your neighbor you’ll be the one boasting at what an amazing deal you found on those jeans. Deo. Never. Miss a deal.
